<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1814,1995]" pageId="9" pageNumber="25">
<taxonomicName box="[151,272,1815,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Svastrides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,272,1815,1840]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="25">Svastrides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a genus that includes only South American species of relatively large 
<taxonomicName box="[1129,1232,1814,1840]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Eucerini">Eucerini</taxonomicName>
. Both sexes have the clypeocular distance about half or more of the width of the flagellum, and the body is covered with abundant pilosity. Additionally, males have very long antennae, often surpassing the basis of T 
<number box="[1265,1281,1892,1918]" pageId="9" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
. Five species are included in 
<taxonomicName box="[341,466,1931,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Svastrides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[341,466,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="25">Svastrides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Jorgensen" authorityName="Jorgensen" box="[484,733,1930,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Svastrides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bauni">
<emphasis box="[484,499,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="25">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[515,584,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="25">bauni</emphasis>
(JÃ¶rgensen)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[750,878,1930,1956]" name="Argentina" pageId="9" pageNumber="25">Argentina</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Urban" authorityName="Urban" box="[899,1069,1930,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Svastrides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neffi">
<emphasis box="[899,914,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="25">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[931,985,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="25">neffi</emphasis>
Urban
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1085,1213,1930,1956]" name="Argentina" pageId="9" pageNumber="25">Argentina</collectingCountry>
